"Abin da zai zama kyakkyawan farawa idan aka ninka kasafin kudin bincike kan AI, ganin cewa duk sauran kasashen sun wuce Amurka kuma ana sa ran samun wani ci gaba a fannin AI", in ji Lee.
Biyu kudade zai iya ninka yiwuwar cewa babban ci gaba na AI zai kasance a Amurka, kamar yadda Lee ya fada a wata hira da CNN wannan makon.
Lee, wanda littafinsa mai suna Artificial Intelligence Superpowers: China, Silicon Valley, da New World Order, Houghton Mifflin Harcourt ya wallafa a wannan watan, shi ne babban darektan Sinovation Ventures, wanda ya zuba jari a daya daga cikin manyan kamfanonin kere kere na kasar Sin, Face ++ .
A shekarun 1980s, a Jami'ar Carnegie Mellon, ya yi aiki a kan tsarin kera kere-kere wanda ya doke dan wasan Amurka mai suna Othello, kuma daga bisani ya zama shugaban kamfanin Microsoft Research da kuma shugaban kamfanin Google na kasar Sin.
Lee ya amince da gasar fasaha ta gwamnatin Amurka ta baya, kamar ta Hukumar Kula da Ayyukan Harkokin Kasuwancin Tsaro, da kuma kokarin taimakawa wajen samun karin mutane masu basira, ya tambayi lokacin da za a yi na gaba.
Lee ya ce masana kimiyya a Amurka suna fama da kalubale wajen samun tallafin gwamnati.
"Ba kasar Sin ce ke karbar shugabannin ilimi ba, kamfanoni ne", in ji Lee.
A cikin 'yan shekarun nan, Facebook da Google da sauran kamfanonin fasaha sun ɗauki ƙwararrun masana kimiyya don yin aiki a kan AI.
Lee ya ce sauye-sauyen manufofin shige da fice na iya taimakawa Amurka wajen karfafa kokarin da take yi na kera fasaha.
"Ina ganin ya kamata a ba da katin kore ta atomatik ga daliban da ke aikin digiri na uku a fannin ilimin kere kere", in ji shi.
A watan Yuli na shekarar 2017, majalisar kasar Sin ta sanar da shirin bunkasa sabuwar fasahar kere kere.
Lee ya kara da cewa, hukumar kimiyya ta kasar Sin tana ba da tallafi ga malamai a cibiyoyin kimiyya, kamar yadda hukumar kimiyya ta kasar Sin da sauran kungiyoyin gwamnati ke ba da tallafi ga masana kimiyya a Amurka, amma ingancin aikin kimiyya a kasar Sin ya kasa.
