HIV/AIDS: Kasar Sin ta ba da rahoton karuwar sabbin cututtuka da kashi 14%
China ta ba da rahoton cewa adadin mutanen da ke fama da cutar HIV da AIDS ya karu da kashi 14 cikin ɗari.
A cewar jami'an lafiya, mutane fiye da 820,000 ne suka kamu da cutar a kasar.
A cikin kwata na biyu na 2018 kadai, an samu sabbin mutane kusan 40 000.
Yawancin sabbin kamuwa da cutar a cikin mutane an kamu da su ta hanyar jima'i, kuma wannan ya bambanta da ƙididdigar da aka samu a baya.
A wasu sassa na kasar Sin, yawan kamuwa da cutar HIV ya bazu ne ta hanyar karbar jini daga wani mutum.
Amma, adadin mutanen da ke da cutar HIV ya ragu zuwa kusan babu , in ji jami'an kiwon lafiya na kasar Sin a wani taro a lardin Yunnan.
Amma da shigewar lokaci, adadin mutanen da ke fama da cutar HIV da AIDS a ƙasar Sin ya ƙaru zuwa 100,000.
Yaduwar cutar kanjamau ta hanyar jima'i lamari ne mai matukar muhimmanci a cikin al'ummar LGBT a kasar Sin.
An haramta luwadi a kasar Sin tun a shekarar 1997, amma nuna bambanci ga LGBT ya zama ruwan dare gama gari.
Domin al'adarmu ta ɗabi'a, kashi 70 zuwa 90 cikin ɗari na maza da suke yin jima'i da maza suna aure.
Yawancin cututtukan da ke tattare da wannan cuta suna faruwa ne domin rashin amfani da kāriya ta wajen yin jima'i.
Tun daga 2003, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta yi alkawarin samar da maganin cutar HIV ga kowa a kasar a matsayin wata hanyar magance matsalar.
